subSubSection.paragraph:
Teeth small, conical, uniserial, slightly retrorse and not close-set (
Fig. 3
). One medial followed by 2 teeth medially and 2 laterally at tip of snout, followed by an intermaxillary rosette of 2 medial and 2 lateral irregular pairs of teeth, followed by a gap, then a single row of 12 small vomerine teeth, decreasing in size posteriorly. Maxilla with 9–10 uniserial teeth on each side. Lower jaw with 11–12 teeth in a single row.
